	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​&lt;/strong&gt;This painting style originated in the &lt;strong&gt;Mithila region of Bihar, India.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Madhubani paintings are made from the paste of powdered rice and use colors derived from plants.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;They often illustrate scenes from &lt;strong&gt;Hindu mythology, as well as scenes of royal courts and social events. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
